  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Livelihood and Market Recovery Assessment For Gender Impact Evaluation in Duma</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Oxfam in coordination with World Food Programme (WFP) is planning to conduct &apos;Market and livelihoods recovery assessment&apos; in Duma district. The study basically focuses to:  Identify and describe different livelihood groups including household assets; the strategies employed to derive food and income and the relationships between households and with the wider economy; and how households use that income to meet their basic needs, for investment or for social obligations. Access the extent to which households have recovered in terms of livelihoods and food security and provide information needed to recognize opportunities for recovery and gaps faced by the households to fully recover. Identification of Livelihood Market disruption, opportunities and constraints within each market system due to conflict and COVID 19 Pandemic, as well as key risks and mitigating measures. Identification of three to four high impact market system dynamics with high potential for recovery and growth specially in COVID 19 context and describes their structure and function within the context.  Provide general and practical recommendations (response options) to support key Livelihoods Recovery and Markets for vulnerable communities and households considering gender and protection aspects; One area of recommendation will also provide support to Policy and Advocacy Actions. Identification of relevant Livelihood and Markets interventions that help in restoring, improving, and developing livelihood and resilience of the most vulnerable communities and households based on criteria of food insecurity, resilience and sustainability. Developing phased -base implementation plan  that will be broken down into three phases, short term, medium term, and long term. , providing project proposal and/or concept note for all potential livelihood and market interventions that help in improving food security of the targeted areas and communities.</narrative>
  </description>
